with you, if
you don't mind.

28:36.348 --> 28:38.116 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RUKMINI CALLIMACHI, The New York
Times: Sure.

28:38.150 --> 28:40.752 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Give us a
status report.
How is ISIS doing right now?
Where are they

28:40.786 --> 28:42.554 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
operating? And how are they
doing?

28:42.588 --> 28:47.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUKMINI CALLIMACHI: They have
certainly lost
some territory both in Iraq and
also more

28:47.259 --> 28:49.361 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
recently in Libya.

28:49.394 --> 28:54.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
