socioeconomically
marginalized areas, the suburbs
of Paris and

30:53.785 --> 30:55.587 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
those of Brussels.

30:55.620 --> 30:59.524 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's a very different type of
recruit from
the more sort of intellectual
types that we

30:59.558 --> 31:01.760 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
saw in al-Qaida 15 years ago.

31:01.793 --> 31:05.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Rukmini, this
seems to fly
in the face of what we -- what
many people

31:05.964 --> 31:11.336 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
believe, that ISIS is largely an
ideologically,
religiously-driven organization.

